description.narrative:
Indicator 1: 
1.1	# of trainings/workshops on GCF requirements for direct and indirect access conducted for national institutions;
1.2	Climate finance task force/coordination mechanism is established and functional;
1.3	# of online platforms established for climate finance information;
1.4	# of knowledge products produced for climate finance information;
1.5	# of entities identified, assessed, and supported for accreditation to the GCF

Indicator 2:
2.1	# of tools developed or tailored for Uzbekistan to assess and/or scale up climate projects and programmes;
2.2	# of tools/checklists developed to prioritise projects and link pipeline to national policies and priorities;
2.3	# of training workshops on GCF pipeline development conducted for public and private sectors;
2.4	# of proposals developed in priority sectors by public and/or private stakeholders

Indicator 3:
3.1	# of national strategies developed and adopted to prioritise and finance adaptation sectors;
3.2	# of studies conducted to assess and identify cost priority actions for LEDS, national adaptation strategy

Indicator 4: 
4.1	# of trainings for LFIs on assessing climate-relevant investment opportunities, climate finance mechanisms;
4.2	# of tools developed and adopted through training by LFIs for evaluating climate change projects;
4.3	# of are established and functional mechanisms to facilitate project development between LFIs, state funds and project developers

Indicator 5:
5.1	Monitoring and Evaluation system is in place;
5.2	Project outputs and outcomes monitored and lessons learned codified

comment.narrative:
Baseline 1: 
1.1	No trainings conducted on GCF requirements and/or coordination of direct and indirect access by national institutions;
1.2	No climate finance coordination mechanism is in place;
1.3	No online platforms established for climate finance information;
1.4	No dedicated knowledge products produced for climate finance information;
1.5	No entities identified, assessed, and supported for accreditation to the GCF

Baseline 2:
2.1	No tools developed or tailored for Uzbekistan to assess and/or scale up climate projects and programmes;
2.2	No tools/checklists developed to prioritise projects and link pipeline to national policies and priorities;
2.3	No trainings on GCF pipeline development for public or private sector stakeholders;
2.4	Limited, if any, proposals developed in priority sectors by public or private sectors for GCF

Baseline 3:
3.1	No national strategies on financing adaptation priorities;
3.2	No studies conducted to cost LEDS or national adaptation strategy

Baseline 4:
4.1	No trainings for LFIs on assessing climate-relevant investment opportunities, climate finance mechanisms;
4.2	No tools developed or adopted by LFIs for use in climate finance investment opportunities;
4.3	No mechanisms established to facilitate public-private cooperation for climate-relevant project development

Baseline 5: 
5.1	No Monitoring and Evaluation system;
5.2	No evaluation of project output and outcomes

Target 1:
1.1	Climate finance task force/coordination mechanism is functional;
1.2	One online platform populated with climate finance information is in place and operational;

Target 2:
2.1 Project pipeline prioritized and linked to national policies and priorities;
2.2 At least two project proposals for GCF pipeline developed by public and/or private stakeholders and adopted by the government; and included into the GCF pipeline

Target 3:
N/A

Target 4:
N/A

Target 5: 
5.1 Monitoring and Evaluation system is operational;
5.2 M&E and adaptive management applied to project in response to the needs, and lessons learned codified
